1
00:00:10,400 --> 00:00:11,467
<i> What happened to you?</i>

2
00:00:11,600 --> 00:00:13,133
<i>Why are you looking suspiciously
at the Taho vendor?</i>

3
00:00:13,267 --> 00:00:15,567
<i>Remember, we recognized
Oppa sniper?</i>

4
00:00:15,700 --> 00:00:16,767
<i> What's in your bag?</i>

5
00:00:16,900 --> 00:00:17,367
<i> This?</i>

6
00:00:20,000 --> 00:00:21,433
<i> Go around, I'll follow him!</i>

7
00:00:21,567 --> 00:00:22,467
<i> Mister, wait a minute!</i>

8
00:00:22,600 --> 00:00:24,233
<i>I was just going to ask you
something.</i>

9
00:00:24,567 --> 00:00:25,867
<i> Stop!</i>

10
00:00:26,000 --> 00:00:26,767
<i> Where did he go?</i>

11
00:00:26,900 --> 00:00:27,833
<i> You, go, go, go!</i>

12
00:00:27,967 --> 00:00:30,167
<i>Don't try to do something bad.
I'm tired!</i>

13
00:00:30,300 --> 00:00:31,133
<i> Move aside! Move!</i>

14
00:00:32,867 --> 00:00:34,033
<i>They're just sending me
the money.</i>

15
00:00:34,200 --> 00:00:34,900
<i>They're just giving me
instructions.</i>

16
00:00:35,033 --> 00:00:35,767
<i> That's all.</i>

17
00:00:35,900 --> 00:00:37,267
<i>Let's talk at the police
station!</i>

18
00:00:57,000 --> 00:00:57,600
<i> Dizon!</i>

19
00:01:02,200 --> 00:01:04,067
<i> Die!</i>

20
00:01:04,200 --> 00:01:05,600
<i>You made a mistake
in challenging me</i>

21
00:01:05,733 --> 00:01:07,300
<i> because I don't give up.</i>

22
00:01:18,833 --> 00:01:21,933
Ernesto Makvar alias Gatilyo.

23
00:01:23,100 --> 00:01:26,600
The one you fought was a known
hitman, Enriquez.

24
00:01:26,967 --> 00:01:28,933
So, Chief, that means he has no
boss,

25
00:01:29,200 --> 00:01:32,033
that he will only act when
someone is willing to pay him.

26
00:01:32,167 --> 00:01:33,467
But he was knocked down.

27
00:01:33,600 --> 00:01:34,667
That means he knows something.

28
00:01:34,800 --> 00:01:35,800
Enriquez is right.

29
00:01:36,067 --> 00:01:37,333
That's why I really want
to catch him.

30
00:01:37,467 --> 00:01:39,367
I'm sure we can squeeze
a lot out of him.

31
00:01:40,200 --> 00:01:42,133
But I really had no choice
earlier.

32
00:01:43,133 --> 00:01:46,467
If I didn't beat him to it,
I'd be the one to die.

33
00:01:46,833 --> 00:01:48,000
That's fine, Conde.

34
00:01:48,133 --> 00:01:49,167
Good job anyway.

35
00:01:50,933 --> 00:01:52,567
If you get any information,

36
00:01:54,000 --> 00:01:55,533
tell me right away.

37
00:01:55,833 --> 00:01:57,433
Go ahead, you're dismissed.

38
00:01:58,333 --> 00:01:59,000
Sir.

39
00:02:03,600 --> 00:02:04,733
I'll go ahead, Enriquez.

40
00:02:04,867 --> 00:02:08,133
It's a shame, Sir, if we had
brought the Korean here alive,

41
00:02:09,400 --> 00:02:13,700
he probably knows a lot of
things, but you killed him.

42
00:02:16,367 --> 00:02:18,333
Is there something you want
to tell me, Enriquez?

43
00:02:18,467 --> 00:02:19,867
I'm just wondering, Sir.

44
00:02:20,333 --> 00:02:23,233
You said earlier that you wanted
to catch the Korean.

45
00:02:24,967 --> 00:02:26,167
Why did you kill him?

46
00:02:26,300 --> 00:02:31,133
Enriquez, I had to choose
between him and me.

47
00:02:32,467 --> 00:02:34,600
Now, if you have a problem
with me, report it to the Chief.

48
00:03:10,267 --> 00:03:11,233
Hello, boss?

49
00:03:12,067 --> 00:03:13,267
Have you heard the news?

50
00:03:15,100 --> 00:03:16,567
That Korean is crazy.

51
00:03:17,067 --> 00:03:18,900
All he does is rant,
but he's good for nothing.

52
00:03:19,267 --> 00:03:21,133
Did you know that Selena
is still alive?

53
00:03:21,467 --> 00:03:24,433
And until now, Sonny's SD card
has not been found.

54
00:03:24,733 --> 00:03:26,000
Boss, just tell me.

55
00:03:27,033 --> 00:03:29,867
Maybe it's time for me to shine.

56
00:03:31,033 --> 00:03:32,767
You saw what I did, right?

57
00:03:35,900 --> 00:03:36,467
Thank you.

58
00:03:38,367 --> 00:03:40,100
- Ma'am?
- Ma'am, Sir...

59
00:03:40,833 --> 00:03:41,833
Do you need something?

60
00:03:44,233 --> 00:03:48,833
I'm sorry, I know we discussed
this at orientation,

61
00:03:49,467 --> 00:03:51,800
but maybe I can ask you a favor.

62
00:03:52,333 --> 00:03:54,967
What is it, Miss Selena?
Is there a problem?

63
00:03:55,133 --> 00:03:56,867
No, I don't have a problem,

64
00:03:57,000 --> 00:04:02,033
but I really need
to make a call.

65
00:04:02,167 --> 00:04:04,900
Maybe you can grant my request.

66
00:04:05,167 --> 00:04:06,400
It's really important.

67
00:04:09,600 --> 00:04:11,333
Oh my, Ma'am, I'm sorry,

68
00:04:11,467 --> 00:04:13,967
but that's really against
our protocol.

69
00:04:15,200 --> 00:04:16,167
Why don't we do this, Ma'am?

70
00:04:16,833 --> 00:04:19,867
We'll be the ones to call
whoever you want to talk to.

71
00:04:20,667 --> 00:04:22,733
Who do you want to talk to,
Ma'am?

72
00:04:23,833 --> 00:04:25,233
No. Okay, thank you.

73
00:04:37,200 --> 00:04:38,333
Hey Bok, thank you.

74
00:04:38,467 --> 00:04:39,133
Bok.

75
00:04:39,267 --> 00:04:39,933
Thank you, Bok.

76
00:04:40,067 --> 00:04:40,633
Cheers.

77
00:04:41,767 --> 00:04:44,767
You know, I told you,
be careful with that Enriquez.

78
00:04:44,900 --> 00:04:45,867
She's hardworking,

79
00:04:46,000 --> 00:04:49,400
but her meddlesome ways
are on a different level.

80
00:04:51,833 --> 00:04:54,033
I don't know what I will do with
that girl.

81
00:04:54,833 --> 00:04:55,900
She's a troublemaker.

82
00:04:56,367 --> 00:04:59,467
No matter what I do,
she doubts it.

83
00:05:03,967 --> 00:05:05,967
Bok, just understand her.

84
00:05:06,333 --> 00:05:08,533
That's how it is,
with the newbies, right?

85
00:05:09,133 --> 00:05:11,200
They want to show off and want
to prove something.

86
00:05:12,700 --> 00:05:15,167
It would be good if she's really
focused on the case.

87
00:05:16,167 --> 00:05:18,967
The problem is, she's looking
at it from a different angle.

88
00:05:19,100 --> 00:05:20,000
It's annoying.

89
00:05:24,133 --> 00:05:28,133
Bok, I have a suggestion,
just so you don't get annoyed.

90
00:05:28,800 --> 00:05:29,733
What?

91
00:05:30,133 --> 00:05:35,500
What if instead of being mean to
her, you try to be nice to her?

92
00:05:36,133 --> 00:05:37,567
Who knows when you two become
okay,

93
00:05:37,700 --> 00:05:38,867
she will no longer bother you?

94
00:05:39,233 --> 00:05:41,833
It's like a good cop,
just a bad cop.

95
00:05:41,967 --> 00:05:42,700
But with you,
the other way around.

96
00:05:42,833 --> 00:05:44,833
From bad cop to good cop, right?

97
00:05:52,900 --> 00:05:54,133
Good morning, Bobby!

98
00:05:54,267 --> 00:05:55,533
Bobby, morning!

99
00:05:56,500 --> 00:05:57,467
What happened there?

100
00:05:57,600 --> 00:05:58,400
Deep in thought.

101
00:05:58,533 --> 00:05:59,000
I thought of something.

102
00:05:59,133 --> 00:05:59,800
What's that?

103
00:06:01,167 --> 00:06:02,367
Hey, it's Sir Tonyo, oh!

104
00:06:02,833 --> 00:06:04,233
Sir Tonyo!

105
00:06:06,133 --> 00:06:07,133
Sir Tonyo?

106
00:06:10,267 --> 00:06:11,800
Look at how she reacts.

107
00:06:11,933 --> 00:06:13,633
She has a long neck.
Is that a giraffe?

108
00:06:15,233 --> 00:06:17,600
You've got nothing to do
with your life, right?

109
00:06:19,333 --> 00:06:22,433
Sis, please, you know,
we get you.

110
00:06:22,567 --> 00:06:24,233
We're like that too,
when we have a crush.

111
00:06:24,367 --> 00:06:26,433
And Bobby, admit it.

112
00:06:27,233 --> 00:06:28,967
It feels good, doesn't it?

113
00:06:29,100 --> 00:06:29,933
Doesn't it?

114
00:06:30,167 --> 00:06:32,333
Especially when your crush
is an action star!

115
00:06:32,467 --> 00:06:33,100
Yes.

116
00:06:33,233 --> 00:06:33,767
That's right.

117
00:06:33,900 --> 00:06:34,333
Doesn't it?

118
00:06:36,133 --> 00:06:37,800
Stop it, you two!

119
00:06:38,367 --> 00:06:39,533
He will not come here.

120
00:06:40,700 --> 00:06:41,933
- You're not sure.
- Okay.

121
00:06:42,200 --> 00:06:46,000
Hey, you two,
you're making so much noise.

122
00:06:46,133 --> 00:06:46,933
Grandmother,
scold them go there.

123
00:06:47,067 --> 00:06:49,033
- Stay there. Over there.
- Kapitana.

124
00:06:49,167 --> 00:06:50,000
Grandchild, how are you?

125
00:06:50,133 --> 00:06:51,233
Are those people bothering you?

126
00:06:52,100 --> 00:06:52,867
Are you okay?

127
00:06:53,000 --> 00:06:54,133
I'm okay.

128
00:06:54,567 --> 00:06:56,333
I'm just thinking a lot of
things, Grandmother.

129
00:06:56,467 --> 00:06:57,200
Oh, really?

130
00:06:57,333 --> 00:06:58,433
Bobby!

131
00:06:58,967 --> 00:07:00,633
It's Sir Tonyo!

132
00:07:02,167 --> 00:07:02,933
You're so annoying!

133
00:07:03,067 --> 00:07:04,567
Didn't I tell you he won't come
here?

134
00:07:04,700 --> 00:07:06,100
Okay.

135
00:07:06,533 --> 00:07:08,867
What if he's here?
What are you going to do?

136
00:07:09,000 --> 00:07:09,533
Yes.

137
00:07:09,833 --> 00:07:10,833
Yes, okay.

138
00:07:10,967 --> 00:07:14,667
When he's really there
and comes here, I'll treat you!

139
00:07:14,833 --> 00:07:16,433
Okay, okay, deal.

140
00:07:16,567 --> 00:07:17,233
Okay!

141
00:07:17,367 --> 00:07:18,333
Deal.

142
00:07:18,467 --> 00:07:19,533
Kapitana, you're our witness,
right?

143
00:07:19,667 --> 00:07:21,333
You guys are just fooling us.

144
00:07:21,633 --> 00:07:24,133
You guys, you're making
a lot of noise, the neighbors.

145
00:07:24,267 --> 00:07:25,067
Okay.

146
00:07:25,300 --> 00:07:26,067
Surprise...

147
00:07:26,633 --> 00:07:27,233
Check it.

148
00:07:27,367 --> 00:07:28,567
Just check it.

149
00:07:28,900 --> 00:07:29,800
You don't want to believe.

150
00:07:29,933 --> 00:07:30,767
Enriquez.

151
00:07:33,267 --> 00:07:34,333
Sir Tonyo?

152
00:07:39,100 --> 00:07:42,433
The power of the sun!

153
00:07:42,667 --> 00:07:45,600
It contains light.

154
00:07:46,200 --> 00:07:48,867
Twins, be strong.

155
00:07:49,033 --> 00:07:51,700
We are the Super twins!

156
00:07:52,967 --> 00:07:53,733
Told you!

157
00:07:56,200 --> 00:07:57,000
Tonyo!

158
00:07:57,133 --> 00:07:58,033
Come in!

159
00:07:58,567 --> 00:08:01,833
I cooked, stay and eat here.
I'll prepare the table for you.

160
00:08:01,967 --> 00:08:02,900
No need, thanks.

161
00:08:03,300 --> 00:08:04,967
I am here to fetch
your granddaughter.

162
00:08:11,133 --> 00:08:12,500
Why, Sir?

163
00:08:12,633 --> 00:08:13,533
Where are we going?

164
00:08:13,800 --> 00:08:16,200
I'll just take you with me
and we'll talk to Daga

165
00:08:16,967 --> 00:08:18,767
about Victor Santiago.

166
00:08:21,267 --> 00:08:23,867
In the formal complaint
filed by incumbent

167
00:08:24,000 --> 00:08:25,800
Mayor Joaquin "El Hepe" Guerrero

168
00:08:25,933 --> 00:08:30,333
against the alleged hostage
situation of mayoral candidate

169
00:08:30,467 --> 00:08:35,667
Victor "Amo" Santiago,
whistleblower Brando Salazar,

170
00:08:35,800 --> 00:08:36,867
alias Daga,
will play a big role,

171
00:08:37,000 --> 00:08:39,333
especially if the Court
subpoenas him.

172
00:08:40,633 --> 00:08:43,567
Amo, Amo, it's VM.

173
00:08:45,233 --> 00:08:46,433
VM, hello.

174
00:08:48,967 --> 00:08:50,700
Vice, you're here.

175
00:08:51,000 --> 00:08:51,533
Amo.

176
00:08:51,967 --> 00:08:54,667
I'm sure you want to talk

177
00:08:56,233 --> 00:08:59,667
about the latest character
assassination against me.

178
00:09:00,700 --> 00:09:05,600
Look, Amo, I understand
that politics is really dirty.

179
00:09:05,733 --> 00:09:08,000
That's why I stayed this long in
politics,

180
00:09:08,700 --> 00:09:13,233
because I do my best to steer
clear of dirty things

181
00:09:13,500 --> 00:09:14,800
but I'm sorry, Amo.

182
00:09:14,933 --> 00:09:18,767
I need to disassociate my name
from your candidacy.

183
00:09:19,200 --> 00:09:21,133
No, no, you can't do this.

184
00:09:22,133 --> 00:09:23,100
Now really?

185
00:09:23,367 --> 00:09:24,633
We have an agreement.

186
00:09:25,233 --> 00:09:29,700
Amo, we didn't talk about this
kind of exposés

187
00:09:29,867 --> 00:09:31,200
against your name.

188
00:09:32,100 --> 00:09:33,233
I'm sorry, Victor.

189
00:09:34,167 --> 00:09:36,000
I value CNL's backing.

190
00:09:36,633 --> 00:09:39,667
It's my responsibility
to take care of their vote.

191
00:09:42,100 --> 00:09:43,033
I'm sorry, Amo.

192
00:09:45,300 --> 00:09:49,233
Don't tell me you're going
to endorse Joaquin.

193
00:09:54,433 --> 00:09:55,567
I'm not sure.

194
00:09:57,000 --> 00:09:57,600
We'll see.

195
00:10:04,733 --> 00:10:07,400
Are you wondering, Enriquez,
why I fetch you?

196
00:10:07,933 --> 00:10:08,867
Not at all, Sir.

197
00:10:10,067 --> 00:10:12,867
I just thought Lieutenant Garcia
was the one you were with

198
00:10:13,000 --> 00:10:14,200
in the investigation of Daga.

199
00:10:14,333 --> 00:10:16,800
I just thought it would be
better if you could hear

200
00:10:16,933 --> 00:10:21,367
what Daga had to say
for transparency, right?

201
00:10:23,533 --> 00:10:25,467
I don't know what we'll get out
of it,

202
00:10:26,633 --> 00:10:29,033
but I hope it helps in the case
we're investigating.

203
00:10:59,000 --> 00:10:59,933
Enriquez.

204
00:11:11,267 --> 00:11:12,600
Good morning, Grandmother.

205
00:11:14,000 --> 00:11:15,333
Good morning.

206
00:11:15,933 --> 00:11:17,100
What's that, hija?

207
00:11:17,767 --> 00:11:19,033
Can I ask, Grandmother?

208
00:11:19,667 --> 00:11:20,433
What's that, hija?

209
00:11:22,067 --> 00:11:25,100
Do you know where Brando
Salazar, alias Daga, lives?

210
00:11:26,933 --> 00:11:28,167
Are you police officers?

211
00:11:30,333 --> 00:11:32,100
We just wanted to talk to him

212
00:11:32,633 --> 00:11:35,167
about what he said
about Victor Santiago.

213
00:11:36,967 --> 00:11:38,033
I'm sorry.

214
00:11:39,633 --> 00:11:40,400
Well, I don't know him.

215
00:11:40,533 --> 00:11:42,033
No, I don't know anything like
that.

216
00:11:42,333 --> 00:11:43,400
Just ask around there...

217
00:11:43,533 --> 00:11:44,333
Over there.

218
00:11:44,900 --> 00:11:46,300
I'm sorry.

219
00:11:47,300 --> 00:11:48,333
Okay, thank you.

220
00:11:54,533 --> 00:11:56,267
It looks like we're not going
to get anywhere here.

221
00:11:59,733 --> 00:12:01,033
Let's go in, Sir.

222
00:12:17,200 --> 00:12:18,467
What's your problem with me?

223
00:12:21,600 --> 00:12:22,400
What's your problem?

224
00:12:22,533 --> 00:12:23,433
Hey...

225
00:12:58,200 --> 00:12:59,667
Good morning, guys.

226
00:13:00,300 --> 00:13:01,333
Good morning.

227
00:13:02,300 --> 00:13:04,267
I'm Lieutenant Conde.

228
00:13:04,533 --> 00:13:06,367
Sergeant Enriquez is with me.

229
00:13:08,967 --> 00:13:10,467
Good morning.

230
00:13:11,167 --> 00:13:14,267
Boys, please be respectful
of our guests.

231
00:13:14,600 --> 00:13:17,533
We were just wondering
if you know anyone named Brando,

232
00:13:18,100 --> 00:13:19,333
Brando Salazar.

233
00:13:21,733 --> 00:13:23,267
That's an old name!

234
00:13:23,400 --> 00:13:25,567
Hey, maybe that's your father!

235
00:13:25,700 --> 00:13:27,800
No, his father's name
is Wilfredo.

236
00:13:32,033 --> 00:13:33,600
He's better known as Daga.

237
00:13:37,667 --> 00:13:39,000
You're on another level,
Miss Mira.

238
00:13:39,433 --> 00:13:40,333
You're unreachable.

239
00:13:40,667 --> 00:13:41,767
What's with you?

240
00:13:41,900 --> 00:13:43,900
You just have to be at the right
place and the right time.

241
00:13:44,033 --> 00:13:46,433
Your source is also good,
really reliable.

242
00:13:46,800 --> 00:13:48,233
That's why I'll take care
of you.

243
00:13:48,367 --> 00:13:50,633
We'll both succeed as long
as you work with me, okay?

244
00:13:50,767 --> 00:13:51,233
Sure.

245
00:13:51,367 --> 00:13:52,233
Mayor, good morning.

246
00:13:52,367 --> 00:13:54,600
Hey, morning, morning.

247
00:13:54,767 --> 00:13:55,833
You're something else,
Miss Mira.

248
00:13:55,967 --> 00:13:58,800
Morning, morning.

249
00:13:59,167 --> 00:14:02,400
We need to talk to him about
that exposé she gave

250
00:14:02,533 --> 00:14:03,800
to Victor Santiago.

251
00:14:04,067 --> 00:14:05,433
Hey, I recognize them.

252
00:14:06,100 --> 00:14:08,200
Those are the ones who helped in
the riot in the court.

253
00:14:09,533 --> 00:14:10,100
That's them?

254
00:14:10,233 --> 00:14:11,133
Yes, that's them.

255
00:14:13,433 --> 00:14:14,400
Is that true?

256
00:14:15,367 --> 00:14:17,333
Are you the police who helped
with the riot in the court?

257
00:14:18,667 --> 00:14:19,300
That's us.

258
00:14:21,233 --> 00:14:22,667
Do you want to talk to Daga?

259
00:14:24,233 --> 00:14:25,000
We hope so.

260
00:14:28,733 --> 00:14:33,400
That's fine, but we have a law
to enforce here.

261
00:14:34,333 --> 00:14:36,833
Now, if you really want to talk
to Daga,

262
00:14:40,733 --> 00:14:41,933
surrender those...

263
00:14:43,367 --> 00:14:44,000
You know.

264
00:14:44,867 --> 00:14:45,367
Sorry.

265
00:14:45,633 --> 00:14:47,267
You don't know, but in our area,

266
00:14:47,400 --> 00:14:48,600
there's a bit of a gun ban
right now.

267
00:14:48,733 --> 00:14:50,067
That's why it's not allowed,
right?

268
00:14:50,200 --> 00:14:51,167
Aren't they forbidden?
It's forbidden.

269
00:14:51,300 --> 00:14:53,600
That's forbidden because you'll
never know, right?

270
00:14:56,467 --> 00:14:59,867
But if you don't want to,
we are understanding, right?

271
00:15:00,000 --> 00:15:00,533
Let's go.

272
00:15:00,667 --> 00:15:02,667
Okay, you can leave now.

273
00:15:03,600 --> 00:15:04,400
Wait, wait a minute.

274
00:15:08,233 --> 00:15:09,667
Sir, that's dangerous.

275
00:15:15,500 --> 00:15:16,133
Chief.

276
00:15:18,433 --> 00:15:19,633
Don't point it at me.

277
00:15:25,133 --> 00:15:25,767
That's it.

278
00:15:30,467 --> 00:15:33,367
Now, of course,
before the meet and greet,

279
00:15:33,800 --> 00:15:36,567
before you meet the star
of the day...

280
00:15:39,933 --> 00:15:40,700
Okay.

281
00:15:42,100 --> 00:15:43,167
Wait, what's this?

282
00:15:43,300 --> 00:15:45,700
Easy, easy, Ma'am.
Ma'am, Sir, easy.

283
00:15:47,700 --> 00:15:48,500
Remember?

284
00:15:48,867 --> 00:15:49,900
We have laws here.

285
00:15:50,500 --> 00:15:51,767
Of course, you need
to be blindfolded.

286
00:15:52,167 --> 00:15:53,033
Just relax!

287
00:15:53,800 --> 00:15:54,700
Remember?

288
00:15:54,833 --> 00:15:55,833
Gun ban.

289
00:15:56,900 --> 00:15:57,900
Safe.

290
00:16:02,500 --> 00:16:03,467
Is that secured?

291
00:16:03,600 --> 00:16:04,933
Maybe, it's still visible to
them.

292
00:16:06,267 --> 00:16:07,267
Assist them.

293
00:16:11,567 --> 00:16:12,300
Hey, Mayor!

294
00:16:13,333 --> 00:16:13,833
Major.

295
00:16:16,133 --> 00:16:18,067
Good morning.

296
00:16:18,700 --> 00:16:19,433
Major Morning, morning.

297
00:16:19,567 --> 00:16:20,667
- Good morning.
- You're my idol.

298
00:16:20,800 --> 00:16:22,333
Is it okay to take a picture?

299
00:16:22,467 --> 00:16:23,700
Yes, yes.

300
00:16:23,833 --> 00:16:25,000
Let's take a picture, Sir.

301
00:16:27,133 --> 00:16:27,967
Just a selfie for...

302
00:16:28,100 --> 00:16:28,667
Okay.

303
00:16:28,800 --> 00:16:30,333
Sir, come on. Selfie.

304
00:16:31,367 --> 00:16:32,933
Let's go.

305
00:16:33,067 --> 00:16:33,567
Excuse me.

306
00:16:33,733 --> 00:16:34,533
You. Us.

307
00:16:35,133 --> 00:16:36,167
One, two...

308
00:16:38,367 --> 00:16:39,733
Thank you.

309
00:16:39,867 --> 00:16:42,000
Mayor, what can I do for you?

310
00:16:43,433 --> 00:16:44,833
By the way, Major,

311
00:16:45,400 --> 00:16:48,967
are you aware that I filed
a formal complaint

312
00:16:49,100 --> 00:16:50,967
