Victor Santiago nonsense.

316
00:17:03,567 --> 00:17:04,400
Okay, Mayor.

317
00:17:05,133 --> 00:17:06,133
Let's go to the office.

318
00:17:06,267 --> 00:17:06,967
Okay.

319
00:17:13,500 --> 00:17:14,267
Daga!

320
00:17:16,033 --> 00:17:17,433
You're preparing something.

321
00:17:17,933 --> 00:17:21,100
By the way, you have a visitor.

322
00:17:26,700 --> 00:17:27,500
Hey!

323
00:17:28,933 --> 00:17:29,867
It's you.

324
00:17:30,633 --> 00:17:31,533
Sit down. Sit down.

325
00:17:32,800 --> 00:17:33,633
Which one are we?

326
00:17:34,067 --> 00:17:37,000
The one I called pig during
the hostage taking.

327
00:17:38,267 --> 00:17:39,100
I'm sorry.

328
00:17:39,433 --> 00:17:40,333
That was just acting.

329
00:17:40,833 --> 00:17:41,333
Sit down.

330
00:17:42,300 --> 00:17:43,100
It's okay.

331
00:17:45,600 --> 00:17:47,400
You said you wanted to talk
to me.

332
00:17:49,767 --> 00:17:51,067
Why are you hiding, Daga?

333
00:17:51,467 --> 00:17:53,433
Are you afraid of someone?

334
00:17:55,233 --> 00:17:57,467
You know that Amo can be
influential.

335
00:17:58,700 --> 00:17:59,733
Just playing it safe.

336
00:18:00,000 --> 00:18:01,000
It's hard.

337
00:18:02,767 --> 00:18:05,367
Well, if someone tries to take
your life, we can protect you.

338
00:18:10,133 --> 00:18:10,967
Oh my.

339
00:18:13,300 --> 00:18:17,500
Here in my territory,
no one can touch me.

340
00:18:18,933 --> 00:18:21,800
But of course,
don't tell them I'm here.

341
00:18:26,333 --> 00:18:27,000
Of course.

342
00:18:27,300 --> 00:18:30,000
Victor Santiago's payment
to your group,

343
00:18:31,367 --> 00:18:32,300
what proof do you have for that?

344
00:18:40,067 --> 00:18:40,933
Well, this!

345
00:18:41,600 --> 00:18:43,067
This is the first time
I was able to have this.

346
00:18:43,200 --> 00:18:44,133
This too.

347
00:18:44,533 --> 00:18:48,900
That gun is new, we bought it.
And him, I paid off his debt.

348
00:18:49,033 --> 00:18:49,500
He is a beast.

349
00:18:49,900 --> 00:18:50,567
Yes.

350
00:18:52,433 --> 00:18:54,500
All that, from Amo?

351
00:18:59,300 --> 00:19:01,033
We have no receipts to show,

352
00:19:01,167 --> 00:19:03,833
except for the ones we bought
with Amo's payment,

353
00:19:04,267 --> 00:19:05,967
but all I can tell you is,

354
00:19:07,867 --> 00:19:09,100
I'm not a liar.

355
00:19:09,700 --> 00:19:11,767
Why would I mess up my life?

356
00:19:14,133 --> 00:19:15,867
Is Amo the only one you've met?

357
00:19:16,633 --> 00:19:19,767
Didn't you talk to anyone else
from Amo's camp?

358
00:19:22,067 --> 00:19:26,767
None, but I saw someone
with Amo.

359
00:19:29,000 --> 00:19:31,200
<i> Okay, Amo, we'll go ahead.</i>

360
00:19:31,333 --> 00:19:31,933
<i> Okay, okay.</i>

361
00:19:33,000 --> 00:19:34,400
Amo, can we use your restroom?

362
00:19:34,533 --> 00:19:35,533
Sure, okay.

363
00:19:36,467 --> 00:19:38,733
<i> I'll go first. Okay.</i>

364
00:19:57,400 --> 00:19:59,267
But it had nothing to do
with the riot.

365
00:20:01,867 --> 00:20:02,833
Do you know him?

366
00:20:05,500 --> 00:20:06,033
No.

367
00:20:07,400 --> 00:20:08,800
I haven't met him.

368
00:20:08,933 --> 00:20:10,567
I just saw him with Amo.

369
00:20:10,700 --> 00:20:11,967
He must be his driver.

370
00:20:13,600 --> 00:20:16,633
But I seem to remember his face.

371
00:20:18,467 --> 00:20:20,333
Better yet, Daga, let's go to
the police station.

372
00:20:20,467 --> 00:20:22,300
Describe the person you're
talking about there

373
00:20:22,433 --> 00:20:23,500
so we can make a sketch.

374
00:20:23,633 --> 00:20:24,900
Boss, take it easy.

375
00:20:25,033 --> 00:20:25,433
Just stay there.

376
00:20:25,600 --> 00:20:26,067
Sit down for now.

377
00:20:26,200 --> 00:20:27,667
We're still talking.

378
00:20:27,800 --> 00:20:28,733
Just sit down.

379
00:20:29,800 --> 00:20:31,233
And what did I tell you?

380
00:20:32,133 --> 00:20:33,933
I'll just stay here
in my territory.

381
00:20:34,533 --> 00:20:35,400
Why would I go out?

382
00:20:35,967 --> 00:20:37,933
I'm just letting you talk to me.

383
00:20:38,433 --> 00:20:40,767
I don't trust the police.

384
00:20:41,900 --> 00:20:43,900
Who knows if Amo has an ally
in your force?

385
00:20:48,067 --> 00:20:50,667
What if I send someone here
to sketch?

386
00:20:51,633 --> 00:20:52,600
Is that okay?

387
00:20:57,367 --> 00:20:59,067
It's up to you.

388
00:21:03,333 --> 00:21:05,133
Okay, send him here.

389
00:21:14,833 --> 00:21:15,633
Hello, Dylan?

390
00:21:18,500 --> 00:21:20,800
Daga, you have a visitor.

391
00:21:20,933 --> 00:21:23,400
Boss, where are you taking me?

392
00:21:23,533 --> 00:21:24,400
Is this your contact?

393
00:21:25,433 --> 00:21:26,300
Okay, take off the blindfold.

394
00:21:30,533 --> 00:21:31,167
Dylan.

395
00:21:33,200 --> 00:21:35,433
Daga, Dylan, sketch artist.

396
00:21:36,533 --> 00:21:37,867
How do we do this?

397
00:21:39,667 --> 00:21:42,133
Just describe it to me
and I'll take care of it.

398
00:21:44,733 --> 00:21:46,433
Come on, let's go there.

399
00:21:54,667 --> 00:21:57,333
Let's start with the shape
of his head.

400
00:21:57,700 --> 00:22:00,300
His face looks a little round.

401
00:22:01,633 --> 00:22:02,733
A little rounder.

402
00:22:09,033 --> 00:22:11,467
Good morning, Mayor.
Hey. Good morning.

403
00:22:12,367 --> 00:22:14,967
What are you doing here
at the police station?

404
00:22:16,633 --> 00:22:18,900
No, I just want to show the
people here

405
00:22:19,033 --> 00:22:21,900
that someone still cares
about them.

406
00:22:22,033 --> 00:22:23,667
I just want to clarify,

407
00:22:23,967 --> 00:22:28,300
are you saying that you're going
to focus more on curbing crime

408
00:22:28,433 --> 00:22:30,667
in Calabari now than
campaigning?

409
00:22:31,033 --> 00:22:31,700
That's right.

410
00:22:32,500 --> 00:22:34,667
I'm willing to sacrifice my
campaign

411
00:22:35,267 --> 00:22:38,367
just to curb crime here
in Calabari.

412
00:22:38,633 --> 00:22:41,133
You know, people from Calabari
are smart.

413
00:22:41,367 --> 00:22:44,233
They want to see some work done,

414
00:22:44,367 --> 00:22:48,200
it's hard if I go around here
in the campaign,

415
00:22:48,333 --> 00:22:50,833
and Calabari is not doing okay.

416
00:22:53,500 --> 00:22:54,300
Oh, okay.

417
00:22:54,667 --> 00:22:55,633
- I'll go ahead.
- Thank you.

418
00:22:55,767 --> 00:22:56,733
Thank you very much.

419
00:22:56,867 --> 00:22:57,967
Good morning, Mayor.

420
00:22:59,567 --> 00:23:00,667
Did you get it?

421
00:23:02,900 --> 00:23:04,533
A little thicker, boss,
his eyebrows.

422
00:23:04,667 --> 00:23:05,233
Okay.

423
00:23:07,067 --> 00:23:07,633
Borrow?

424
00:23:08,267 --> 00:23:08,900
Like that?

425
00:23:12,267 --> 00:23:13,133
This is it.

426
00:23:13,267 --> 00:23:14,167
That's him.

427
00:23:14,633 --> 00:23:16,033
This is Amo's driver.

428
00:23:17,000 --> 00:23:17,900
You're good.

429
00:23:18,033 --> 00:23:20,467
Maybe we can use to do a selfie.

430
00:23:20,600 --> 00:23:21,967
There are four of us.

431
00:23:23,033 --> 00:23:25,333
But a portrait, okay?

432
00:23:25,467 --> 00:23:26,467
Do you know this, Sir?

433
00:23:27,500 --> 00:23:28,167
Sure.

434
00:23:28,300 --> 00:23:28,500
Sure.

435
00:23:28,633 --> 00:23:28,967
Okay.

436
00:23:29,100 --> 00:23:29,867
You're good.

437
00:23:36,200 --> 00:23:37,967
We'd better take that
to the station

438
00:23:38,100 --> 00:23:39,267
